<br>
I would get 61 for two things... Divine Arbitration and the 61 vendor spell Supernal Remedy.  Those two things are honestly game changing.  I don't know how I lived without them.  That said, there are worthwhile Class abilities.  I'd recommend Cel Regen and SCRM the most however both have prerequisite archetype abilities.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Class Specific Abilities</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bestow Divine Aura</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Celestial Regeneration</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Divine Resurrection <br>
Innate Invisibility to Undead<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mass Group Buff</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Purify Soul  <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Spell Casting Reinforcement Mastery</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Turn Undead<br>
<br>
I bolded the ones I have so you know which I have an informed opinion on and which is hearsay...<br>
<br>
Bestow Divine Aura I like.  It allows me to free up a slot where I used to have to always keep DA.  I occasionally unmem DA for a nuke now since I know that I have that available if I need it.  It is also instant cast so can't be interupted.<br>
<br>
Celestial Regeneration I LOVE.  Definately worth it.  It heals 250 and can be increased to 275 and 300/tick with additional AA.  Even at 250, this is a fantastic AA.  Free group heal every 15 minutes.  Depending what other AA you have it can last up to 12 ticks (SCRM).<br>
<br>
Divine Resurrection I'll probably get soon.  Didn't think it worth it before they changed the reuse but with new timer it seems a nice ability.  I really don't miss it not having it though.<br>
<br>
Innate Invisibility to Undead I'll probably get someday.  Seems like it would be useful.  Nothing I'm in a huge hurry for however.<br>
<br>
Mass Group Buff I wouldn't get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>unless</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you are either one of the highest or the only cleric in your guild or people you usually raid with.  You can only MGB aego at 60 so you'll never be asked to use it.  Exception to this is if you are doing PoP raids - it is common there to MGB EE which is a level 60 vendor spell so worth getting.  If you are a raider, you want this soon... if not 9 points are better spent elsewhere.<br>
<br>
Purify Soul can only be used once every half hour.  Probably nice to have but Radiant Cure which can be used every three minutes is much better in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Spell Casting Reinforcement Mastery I LOVE.  50% extended buffs are nice but 50% extended HoTs are fantastic.  My HoT heals 3k which makes it mana efficient to use and a lot less agro than any other heal I could use.  500/tick on inc for the chanter when I see multiple mobs and I usually don't have to worry about them again.  Or HoT chanter, HoT tank, Remedy Chanter, all better.  That works without SCRM but getting the extra 1k worth of healing from it makes it mana efficient as well.<br>
<br>
Turn Undead from what I understand is a complete and total waste.  I don't have it personally but I've never heard from anyone who is happy with it.  The problem seems to be that there is a fear component and a DoT component but when the fear part is resisted the DoT stops working as well.  So lots of times the mob is either imune completely or resists after one or two ticks and you then can't reuse it for over an hour.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PoP Ability</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
Divine Arbitration &amp; Radiant Cure - get level one in these ASAP.  <br>
<br>
Divine Arb in my opinion ties with Spell Casting Mastery as the best AAs a cleric can have.  Get 61 and you will almost never lose a chanter again.  You can remedy and heal 1500 HPs in 1.7 seconds or DvA in 0.7 seconds and average the whole groups hit points.  <br>
<br>
Radiant Cure will partially heal slow, will sometimes cure root or snare, will cure tash... I use it a LOT in LDoN but I also used it often before.  This won't be game changing like DvA but still a very good way to spend two points.<br>
<br>
Whatever you do is right though.  Only you know how you play your character so only you know what fits your playstyle.  Gave you answers that fits mine... hope it helps. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane<BR>
