<br>
MGB is nice if you raid.  By definition kinda useless in the grouping world.<br>
<br>
Celestial Regen is fantastic, in both the group and raiding world.  It's free, it's a big heal (over big time), and you can MGB it.  (Tald's numbers are outdated, that's what it was before it went group, it's 250/275/300 per tick now)<br>
<br>
SCRM is just great, works on so many things (extended Yaulp is tasty)<br>
<br>
BDA is sorta handy, usually to use on yourself due to the instant cast thing.  Best when used on concert with CeleRegen.<br>
<br>
Purify Soul is handy when you fight stuff that sticks some serious stuff on that Radient Cure doesn't touch.  Refresh timer is much better now, but still not fantastic like RC.<br>
<br>
Divine Rez is much much better with the new refresh timer.  Best when not used for the exp gain, but rather to get a caster (often yourself) FM after rez/loot.<br>
<br>
Innate IVU more or less serves as a way to kill your hammer pet.  Not many areas where there's just undead, so yea.<br>
<br>
