<br>
SCR and SCRM and Pacification.<br>
<br>
There is this wondrous, wondrous spell you get at 65 called Pacification.  It's the upgrade to pacify, level cap 65 inclusive (so you can use it to pacify L65 mobs but not 66), and the duration is 42 seconds, but see, this is weird, because it's a beneficial spell, but sometimes when you resist, mobs aggro.  That leads me to believe it's actually two spells, one that is beneficial and one that is detrimental.  Now, you can go cast pacification on say a spider in PoN, and sit next to it for 4 minutes and 59 seconds and it will not attack.  As soon as the clock hits 5 minutes after you cast Pacification on it, it's going to attack.  This leads me to believe that the detrimental portion of the spell lasts 42 seconds as described (and if you cast it on yourself, the icon only stays 7 ticks) but the beneficial part, which lowers aggro radius, lasts 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
Now, a friend of mine got SCR3 or something and discovered that his Pacifications were lasting like 60-some seconds.  Ouch.  So apparently, when you get SCR, it ruins the nice long pacification durations.<br>
<br>
If you don't pull, don't like to pull, don't like to sneak past level 61-65 mobs which could chomp you to bits in 5 seconds in order to go places most clerics don't belong, or like to surgically cut through the yard trash in a dungeon in order to pick out the named mobs, then you probably don't care, and go right ahead with SCR and SCRM.  But, in my grinding/farming group, that's now my job for the sole reason that I didn't take SCR or SCRM, and won't until either pacification gets nerfed to 42 seconds without SCR, or until SCR/M stop breaking 5 minute pacifications.  Note: if you already have started SCR, you may as well finish them... 5 minute pacifications only occur without any SCR or SCRM.<br>
<br>
Oh um, I'd also add, get Combat Agility 3, and Channeling Focus 3 if you like to melee.  Eventually you can go around soloing stuff that hits for 300 and has 15k hps.<br>
<br>
And whomever said get 61 for SR above is totally right on.  SR is the win.  Sure, 1522 doesn't sound great, but how about when it's landing for say 1800-2100 and critting for 3600-3900ish, and casts in 1.75 seconds?  It's delicious.  Especially with the healing adept and gift penrif was talking about (love those AAs).<br>
<br>
Also, if you raid, or do crazy stuff with a small group, and can get your hands on the spell Divine Intervention, then Unfailing Divinity is cool, but it needs 61+ I think (probably 61, 63 and 65).<br>
<br>
I mapped out all the AAs I really really want and the list reaches 325 or something.  That's not even with tradeskill AAs or AAs for increasing stats or resists etc.  I can get up to over 500 that I think are worth working on.  Sure, innate wisdom is useless if you have gear that puts you over 355 wisdom, but when you're dead and on a CR, you go back to 100-some wisdom, and +30 would be kind of nice.  About the only things I'd never really want to spend points in except if I was max xp in 65 and had everything else filled would be Innate Intelligence (does nothing for us) and maybe Innate Agility, but even then you'd get a couple points of AC out of it.<br>
